white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Item description: 16mm dia HT bars to BS4449, in col</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"/></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Unit of Measure: Weight (kg)</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Note: Rebar is calculated in length (m), then multiplied by weight/metre run to obtain the weight.</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"/></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Calculation:</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">4T16: 4 pieces of rebar (“4”), High tensile (“T”), 16mm dia (“16”)</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"/></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Length of vertical part= 3.80 + 0.15 (rf slab thickness) – 2x 0.025 (concrete cover top and bottom) = 3.90 (see page 165)</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Length of horizontal part= 0.30 (see page 165)</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Total length of each rebar= 3.90 + 0.30 = 4.20</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"/></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Number of columns= 4</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Number of rebars per column= 4</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"/></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Total length of rebars in columns= 4 x 4 x 4.20 = 67.20</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"/></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Weight/metre run of 16mm dia bars is 1.579kg/m (Refer to CP97 page 72)</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"/></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Weight of rebars in columns= 67.20 x 1.579 = 106.11</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"/></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"><B>Column Links (page 91) (Blue)</B></SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"/></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Note: Rebar is calculated in length (m), then multiplied by weight/metre run to obtain the weight.</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"/></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Calculation:</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">18R10-200: 18 pieces of rebar (“18”), Mild Steel (“R”), 10mm dia (“10”), 200mm c/c spacing (“200”)</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"/></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Note: When the number of pieces is given, no need to calculate quantity based on c/c spacing.</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"/></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Length of each side= 0.30 – 2 x 0.025 (concrete cover) = 0.25 (see section 1-1 &amp; 2-2 on page 165)</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Length of hook= 20 x 0.01 (diameter of rebar) = 0.20</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"/></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Note: General rule for calculating length of hook is 20 x diameter of rebar</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"/></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Length per link= 4 sides x 0.25 + 0.20 (hook) = 1.20</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"/></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"/></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Length of internal wall 2= 3.35 (from page 134)</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"/></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Since the concrete thickening for the 2 walls will meet at a T junction, need to deduct for the overlap. The overlap length is the “spread” of the thickening. Hence overlap= (300mm (ave. wi.) – 112.5 (brickwall thk)) / 2 = 93.75mm = 0.09m</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"/></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Length of concrete thickening = 5.55 + 3.35 – 0.09 = 8.81</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"/></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"/></DIV></BODY></HTML></div>

letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Height of grd beam= 0.45 – 0.15 (ground slab thickness) = 0.30</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"/></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Volume of concrete to grd beams= 4 x 6.10 x 0.30 x 0.30 = 2.20</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"/></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Width of grd beam= 0.30</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"/></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Volume of concrete to grd beams= 4 x 6.10 x 0.30 x 0.30 = 2.20</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"/></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"/></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Height of formwork (2 outer faces)= 0.45</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"/></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">4T16: 4 pieces of rebar (“4”), High tensile (“T”), 16mm dia (“16”)</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"/></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Length of vertical part= 2.45 + 0.15 + 0.70 – 0.05 (concrete cover on the bottom) = 3.25 (see page 165)</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Length of horizontal part= 0.50 (see page 165)</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Total length of each rebar= 3.25 + 0.50 = 3.75</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"/></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Number of column stumps= 4</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Number of rebars per column stump= 4</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"/></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Total length of rebars in column stump= 4 x 4 x 3.75 = 60.00</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"/></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Weight/metre run of 16mm dia bars is 1.579kg/m (Refer to CP97 page 72)</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"/></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Weight of rebars in column stumps= 60.00 x 1.579 = 94.74</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"/></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Note: Rebar is calculated in length (m), then multiplied by weight/metre run to obtain the weight.</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">10R10-200: 10 pieces of rebar (“10”), Mild Steel (“R”), 10mm dia (“10”), 200mm c/c spacing (“200”)</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"/></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"/></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"/></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Average width of concrete thickening= (200 + 400) / 2 = 300</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"/></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Length of internal wall 1= 6.00 – (2x 225) (wall thk) = 5.55 (from page 134)</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Length of internal wall 2= 3.35 (from page 134)</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"/></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Since the concrete thickening for the 2 walls will meet at a T junction, need to deduct for the overlap. The overlap length is the “spread” of the thickening. Hence overlap= (300mm (ave. wi.) – 112.5 (brickwall thk)) / 2 = 93.75mm = 0.09m</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"/></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Length of concrete thickening = 5.55 + 3.35 – 0.09 = 8.81</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"/></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"/></DIV></BODY></HTML></div>

white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Note: When the number of pieces is given, no need to calculate quantity based on c/c spacing.</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"/></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Length of horizontal sides= 0.30 – 2 x 0.05 (concrete cover) = 0.20 (see section 3-3 on page 166)</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Length of vertical sides= 0.45 – 2 x 0.05 (concrete cover) = 0.35 (see section 3-3 on page 166)</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Length of hook= 20 x 0.01 (diameter of rebar) = 0.20</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"/></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Note: General rule for calculating length of hook is 20 x diameter of rebar</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"/></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Length per stirrup= 2 horizontal sides x 0.20 + 2 vertical sides x 0.35 + 0.20 (hook) = 1.30</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"/></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Number of ground beams= 4</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"/></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"/></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"/></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Rebar “a” is distributed from inside of column to column, excluding concrete cover.</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"/></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Span between insides of columns= 6.70 – 2 x 0.30 (columns) 2 x 0.05 (concrete cover) = 6.00 (see page 167)</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Number of rebars per span= 6.00 / 0.20 (c/c spacing) + 1 = 31 </SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Number of span= 4 (4 sides of the slab)</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"/></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Length of horizontal part of rebar “a”= 1.05 (page 169) – 0.05 (concrete cover on the outside) = 1.00</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Length of vertical part of rebar “a”= 0.45 (grd bm thickness) – 2 x 0.05 (concrete cover top and bottom) = 0.35</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"/></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Length of each rebar “a”= 1.00 + 0.35 = 1.35</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"/></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Total length of rebar “a” in ground slab= 4 x 31 x 1.35 = 167.40</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"/></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"><B>Ground Slab Rebar – “b” distribution bar (page 90) (Green)</B></SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"/></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Item description: 10mm dia HT bars to BS4449, in grd slab</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"/></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Unit of Measure: Weight (kg)</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Note: Rebar is calculated in length (m), then multiplied by weight/metre run to obtain the weight.</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"/></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Calculation:</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">4nos T10-200 (bothway): 4 pieces of rebar (“4”), High tensile (“T”), 10mm dia (“10”), 200mm c/c spacing (“200”)</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"/></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Note: When the number of pieces is given, no need to calculate quantity based on c/c spacing.</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"/></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Length of “b” distribution bar= 6.70 – 2 x 1.05 + 0.20 (Add half spacing to both ends of the bar) = 4.80 (Length is also given on page 169)</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Number of “b” distribution bar per side= 4 (given on page 167)</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Number of sides= 4 (4 sides of the slab)</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"/></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Total length of rebar “b” in ground slab= 4 x 4 x 4.80 = 76.80</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"/></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"><B>Ground Slab Rebar – Overall </B></SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"/></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Weight/metre run of 10mm dia bars is 0.616kg/m (Refer to CP97 page 72)</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"/></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Total weight of rebars in ground slab= (448.80 + 167.40 + 76.80) x 0.616 = 426.89</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"/></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"/></DIV></BODY></HTML></div>

letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Length of vertical part= 0.45 – 2x 0.025 (concrete cover top and bottom) = 0.40 (see page 166)</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Total length of each rebar= 6.65 + 2 x 0.40 = 7.45 </SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"/></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Number of roof beams = 4</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Number of rebars per roof beam= 2 (sets of 2T13) x 2 (in each set, green &amp; red)</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"/></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Total length of rebars in roof beams= 4 x 2 x 2 x 7.45 = 119.20</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"/></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Weight/metre run of 13mm dia bars is 1.042kg/m (Refer to CP97 page 72)</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"/></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Weight of rebars in roof beams= 119.20 x 1.042 = 124.21</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"/></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"><B>Roof Beam Stirrups (page 91) (Blue)</B></SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"/></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Item description: 10mm dia MS bars to BS4449, in stirrups in rf bms</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"/></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Unit of Measure: Weight (kg)</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Note: Rebar is calculated in length (m), then multiplied by weight/metre run to obtain the weight.</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"/></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Calculation:</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">30R10-200: 30 pieces of rebar (“30”), Mild Steel (“R”), 10mm dia (“10”), 200mm c/c spacing (“200”)</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"/></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Note: When the number of pieces is given, no need to calculate quantity based on c/c spacing.</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"/></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Length of horizontal sides= 0.30 – 2 x 0.025 (concrete cover) = 0.25 (see section 3-3 on page 166)</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Length of vertical sides= 0.45 – 2 x 0.025 (concrete cover) = 0.40 (see section 3-3 on page 166)</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Length of hook= 20 x 0.01 (diameter of rebar) = 0.20</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"/></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Note: General rule for calculating length of hook is 20 x diameter of rebar</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"/></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Length per stirrup= 2 horizontal sides x 0.25 + 2 vertical sides x 0.40 + 0.20 (hook) = 1.50</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"/></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Number of roof beams= 4</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Number of stirrups per roof beam= 30</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"/></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Total length of stirrups in roof beams= 4 x 30 x 1.50 = 180.00</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"/></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Weight/metre run of 10mm dia bars is 0.616kg/m (Refer to CP97 page 72)</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"/></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;font-size:16px;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-size:16px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Weight of stirrups in roof beams= 180.00 x 0.616 = 110.88</SPAN></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"/></DIV><DIV STYLE="text-align:left;"><SPAN STYLE="display:inline-block; letter-spacing:0px; white-space:pre-wrap;color:#000000;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"/></DIV></BODY></HTML></div>
